法規內容.條文內容:
A bank that issues stored value cards and cooperates with a non-financial institution for business promotions shall:
(1) Clearly define the rights and obligations between the cooperating parties; 
(2) Ensure that the cooperating party meets the bank’s requirements for secure operation and risk management; 
(3) Control and manage fund transfers of customers and transaction data thereof; 
(4) Not transfer to the non-financial institution all or part of the funds which the bank receives in advance from the stored value cards issued; and 
(5) Other matters as required by the Competent Authority.
